Spanish Garlic Shrimp
  --America's Test Kitchen
  
14 medium garlic cloves, peeled
1 lb large shrimp, peeled, deveined, and tails removed
8 tbsp olive oil, divided
1/2 tsp salt
1 bay leaf
2" piece mild chile (New Mexico), roughly broken, seeds included
1 1/2 tsp sherry vinegar
1 tbsp chopped fresh parsley leaves

Mince 2 garlic cloves; toss with shrimp, 2 tbsp olive oil, and salt in medium bowl. Let shrimp marinate at room temp for 30 min. Meanwhile, smash 4 garlic cloves; heat with remainin oil in 12" skillet over medium low heat, stirring occasionally, until garlic is light golden brown, 4-7 min. Remove pan from eat and allow oil to cool to room temp. Using slotted spoon, remove smashed garlic from skillet and discard. Thinly slice remaining 8 cloves garlic. Return skillet to low heat and add sliced garlic, bay leaf, and chile. Cook, stirring occasionally, until garlic is tender but not browned, 4-7 min. If garlic hasn't begun to sizzle after 3 min, increase heat. Increase heat to medium low; add shrimp with marinade to pan in single layer. Cook shrimp, undisturbed, until oil starts to gently bubble, ~2 min. Using tongs, flip shrimp and continue to cook until almost cooked through, ~2 min longer. Increase heat to high and add sherry vinegar and parsley. Cook, stirring constantly, until shrimp are cooked through and oil is bubbling vigorously, 15-20 s. Serve immediately.


Notes: Can sub sweet paprika for chile, 2 tsp of dry sherry and 1 tsp white vinegar for the sherry vinegar.
